\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces The gallery-2DEG spin phase diagram. (a)~{Stoner} phase diagram of the interlayer gas, built by carrying the {SSH}-type surface-charge model of Radha and Lambrecht~\cite  {RadhaLambrecht2021} into the gallery: in the plane of Na content $x$ and {CoO$_2$} spacing $c$ (right axis, the full-coverage gallery half-width $\Gamma _0(c)$) the gallery band is empty below the carrier turn-on ($\Gamma =2\delta $, dark line); just above it the band is narrow and its density of states high, so the gas is {Stoner}-polarized (red) before widening into a paramagnon-boosted ($S>S^\ast $, amber) and then a plain paramagnetic (blue) metal. The polarized strip hugs the turn-on line. Markers: the monolayer ($6.9$~\r A, $\times $) and bilayer ($9.9$~\r A, $\circ $) hydrates at the physical $x=0.35$; the red bar at $x=1$ marks where the {DFT} cell-integrated moment turns on (Fig.~\ref {fig:spin}), coincident with the well transition and so with the model turn-on. The $\sqrt  {3}\times \sqrt  {3}$ ($x=1/3$) cell is over-polarized in {LSDA} and excluded (the wells shift $<6\%$ under the spin treatment). (b)~Cuts at $x=0.35$: the carrier fraction $q$ per Na and the {Stoner} enhancement $S$ against $c$. The model is an ansatz calibrated to the one on/off hydrate anchor pair; every parameter is source-tagged in the generating script.}}{10}{}}
\newlabel{fig:spinpd}{{10}{10}{}{}{}}
